  "text": "For collecting the CL during luteolysis, 29 normal cyclic German Holstein cows were used for this study. The day of estrus was designated as day 0. Cows (n = 425 for each time point) at the mid luteal phase (days 10-12) were injected with PGF 2a in intramuscular (0 h) (0.5 mg of cloprostenol, 2.0 mL of Estrumate TM , Essex Tierarznei, Munich, Germany), and ovaries were collected by ovariectomy [CITATION_1] through the vagina at 0 ( = before PGF 2a injection), 5, 15, and 30 min and 2 and 12 h. Simultaneous plasma samples were collected by caudal venipuncture for P measurements, and were immediately frozen at 220uC until further analysis.",
